cards.title: Base set Raichu Prerelease Stamp
cards.description: Employee-Only test production (or error print) Prerelease Raichu.

cards.title: Base set Ninetales Missing Damage Error
cards.description: This is a typeset pre-print error where the "80" damage is missing from the Fire Blast attack.

cards.title: Base set Machamp Cosmos Holo
cards.description: This Machamp uses the Cosmos holofoil and was distributed in the 2-Player CD-ROM Starter Set.

cards.title: Base set Ninetales Black Flame on Unlimited Holo
cards.description: The Unlimited set version has a "Black Flame" in the holographic artwork similar to the Shadowless version.

cards.title: Base set Beedrill "D.efending" Error
cards.description: Poison Sting's attack text includes a period in the middle of the word "Defending".

cards.title: Base set Wartotle Evolution Box Error
cards.description: Wartotle is shown in the evolution box instead of Squirtle.

cards.title: Base set Pikachu 1999 Poketour Promo
cards.description: An Austrailia-regional released promo card for the 1999 Poketour.

cards.title: Base set E3 Promo Pikachu
cards.description: E3 Promo version Pikachu where the "Red Cheeks" Pikachu variant was distributed at the conference and the "Yellow Cheeks" was distributed via Nintendo Power.

cards.title: Base set Pikachu Red Cheeks
cards.description: First and Shadowless set version of the limited run "Red Cheeks" Pikachu variant.

cards.title: Base set Diglett Fighting Symbol Error
cards.description: The attack energy cost symbol is rotated 90 degrees on unlimited prints.

cards.title: Base set "U.K. Print" or "U.K. 4th print" 2000 Holos
cards.description: The holo cards in the 4th print of the original Base set that include the copyright "1999-2000" are Alakazam, Blastoise, Chansey, Charizard, Clefairy, Gyarados, Hitmonchan, Machamp, Magneton, Mewtwo, Nidoking, Ninetales, Poliwrath, Raichu, Venusaur, Zapdos

cards.title: Unlimited Edition Jungle Holos Missing Set Stamp
cards.description: The set of holos are missing their expansion symbol Clefable, Electrode, Flareon, Jolteon, Kangaskhan, Mr. Mime, Nidoqueen, Scyther, Snorlax, Vaporeon, Venomoth, Victreebel, Vileplume, Wigglytuff.

cards.title: Fruit by the Foot Jungle Meowth Gold Border
cards.description: The usual yellow card border is replaced with a matte gold.

cards.title: Fossil set Cosmos Holos with 1999 Copyright
cards.description: Employee-Only test production (or error print) Cosmos holos Aerodactyl, Articuno, Ditto, Dragonite, Gengar, Haunter, Hitmonlee, Hypno, Kabutops, Lapras, Magneton, Moltres, Muk, Raichu, Zapdos

cards.title: Fossil Unlimited set Zapdos Corrected Evolution Box
cards.description: The holofoil is corrected to not show the evolution box outline and a second corrected version was released using the Cosmos holofoil pattern.

cards.title: Team Rocket Dark Dragonite Error Missing Holofoil
cards.description: Both the first edition and unlimited prints included card 5/82 without holofoil.

cards.title: Team Rocket Dark Charmeleon Kraft Giveaway Wizards Stamp
cards.description: There is a gold "W" for Wizards of the Coast stamped on the card.

cards.title: Team Rocket Dark Arbok Hong Kong Pokemon League Wizards Stamp
cards.description: There is a gold "W" for Wizards of the Coast stamped on the card.

cards.title: Gym Challenge set Blaine's Charizard with Corrected Symbol
cards.description: The energy symbol is corrected to a fire energy in the Roaring Flames description.

cards.title: Gym Challenge set Rocket's Minefield Gym with Corrected Damage Counters
cards.description: The card description is corrected to say "2 damage counters".

cards.title: Base set 2 Non-holo Charizard Printing Error
cards.description: The Base set 2 Charizard Holographic card is printed without the holofoil.

cards.title: Legendary Collection Theme Deck Non-Holos
cards.description: The Legendary Collection set included three non-holo variants Dark Raichu, Dark Charizard, and Dark Blastoise

cards.title: Legendary Collection Exeggcute Error Shifted Energy
cards.description: The attack energy is shifted up.

cards.title: Expedition "For Position Only" Cards
cards.description: These cards have the test 'For Position Only' printed on Alakazam, Ampharos, Arbok, Blastoise, Charizard, Clefable, Dugtrio

cards.title: Expedition Hole-Punched e-Reader Demo Pichu and Hoppip
cards.description: These cards have a punched hole and either all-glossy or front-glossy face.

cards.title: E3 2002 Expedition Test Print Pichu and Hoppip
cards.description: These cards are test print versions that use the Japanese card back.

cards.title: First Edition Promo Ivy Pikachu
cards.description: There is an unintentional "1st" edition stamp on the promo card.

cards.title: Black Star Promo Dark Persian Missing HP
cards.description: The "60 HP" text is missing from the card.

cards.title: CoroCoro Comics 1999 English Pikachu and Jigglypuff
cards.description: The Japanese Comic, CoroCoro, released two english cards in 1999, glossy "grey star" promos.

cards.title: Black Star Promo Mew with Glossy Finish
cards.description: This version of the Black Star Promo Mew was distributed through Gotta Magazine.

cards.title: WB Kids Promos with Error Stamps
cards.description: There are two error variants where the 'WB Kids' is printed upside down or without gold lettering for Electabuzz, Dragonite, Mewtwo, and Pikachu

cards.title: JR Pokemon Stamp Rally Non-holo Promo Eevee and Meowth
cards.description: The Japanese JR Stamp Rally released two english cards in 2000, non-holo versions of the Black Star promos Eevee and Meowth.

cards.title: Power of One Legendary Birds Corrected Illustrator Error (Naoyo Kimura)
cards.description: The corrected illustrator (Naoyo Kimura) for Zapdos, Moltres, and Articuno.

cards.title: Pokemon Center NY Stamped Black Star Promos
cards.description: There is a "Pokemon Center NY" stamp on Ho-oh and Rapidash.

cards.title: Pokemon League Prerelease Stamp
cards.description: The text "PRERELEASE" is stamped on Clefable, Areodactyl (Brown and Gold), Dark Gyarados, and Misty's Seadra.

cards.title: Duelist and Top Deck Magazine W Wizards Stamp Promos
cards.description: There is a gold "W" for Wizards of the Coast stamped on Kabuto, Misty's Psyduck, Brock's Vulpix, Wartotle, and Pikachu.
